## Events

The `nys-{{componentName}}` component emits the following events:

1. `nys-click`: Emitted when the {{componentName}} is clicked.
2. `nys-focus`: Emitted when the {{componentName}} receives focus.
3. `nys-blur`: Emitted when the {{componentName}} loses focus.

You can listen to these events using JavaScript:

```js
// Select the {{componentName}} component
const {{componentName}} = document.querySelector("nys-{{componentName}}");

// Listen for the 'nys-click' event
{{componentName}}.addEventListener("nys-click", () => {
	console.log("{{capitalize componentName}} clicked");
});

// Listen for the 'nys-focus' event
{{componentName}}.addEventListener("nys-focus", () => {
	console.log("{{capitalize componentName}} is focused");
});

// Listen for the 'nys-blur' event
{{componentName}}.addEventListener("nys-blur", () => {
	console.log("{{capitalize componentName}} lost focus");
});
```

